    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CHINA FORGIVES SOME AFRICAN DEBT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>China promises to cancel as much as $1.2 billion in debt to African countries, though it does not say which countries will benefit; offer represents fraction of money African states owe China (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>China promised that it would cancel as much as $1.2 billion in debt to African countries, though it did not say which countries would benefit. China's trade minister, Shi Guangsheng, told a forum in Beijing on China-Africa cooperation that the offer would be made to heavily indebted poor countries and the least-developed countries. The offer represents a fraction of the money African states owe China.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith</p>
      </block>
